### Test Authentication Endpoints
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code

### 1. Health Check - Should work immediately
GET http://localhost:5000/health

###

### 2. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test1234!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

###

### 3. Login with email/password
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test1234!"
}

###

### 4. Get current user (replace YOUR_TOKEN with the token from login response)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

###

### 5. Test Google OAuth (open in browser)
# http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/google

###

### 6. Refresh token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

###

### 7. Logout
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
